WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:03.090
- Previously on
"Superman & Lois"...

00:03.133 --> 00:05.396
- Let's just focus on
what we came here for: family.

00:05.440 --> 00:07.094
- The Smallville team needs
a strong leader,

00:07.268 --> 00:08.747
and I'd like to fill that role
with you, Lana.

00:08.791 --> 00:10.880
- Something sinister
is going on here.

00:10.923 --> 00:13.143
Edge is giving people
Kryptonian powers

00:13.187 --> 00:16.451
at the same time
some armored lunatic arrives

00:16.494 --> 00:17.800
who knows Superman's real name?

00:17.843 --> 00:19.454
- We need to stop Kal-El

00:19.497 --> 00:21.064
before he does to this world
what he did to mine.

00:21.108 --> 00:22.892
- Your abilities are evolving.

00:22.935 --> 00:24.111
You can heal faster,
but you can still get hurt.

00:24.154 --> 00:25.242
- Clark!

00:25.286 --> 00:27.375
- I hid in the Fortress.

00:28.332 --> 00:31.379
[winds howling]

00:33.120 --> 00:36.123
[loud rumbling]

00:41.302 --> 00:43.347
[whooshing]

00:43.391 --> 00:46.437
[ears ringing, radio
murmurings, horn honking]

00:47.569 --> 00:50.006
- The quiet
in here should help.

00:50.050 --> 00:53.053
[laughter, siren blares]

00:54.924 --> 00:56.665
[noises stop]
- [sighs]

01:01.931 --> 01:03.454
- I think Jordan's hearing
kicked in.

01:03.498 --> 01:06.022
- Yes, his mechanosensations

01:06.066 --> 01:08.111
have become
significantly enhanced.

01:09.112 --> 01:10.287
- How do we stop the pain?

01:10.331 --> 01:11.897
- His auditory perception

01:11.941 --> 01:14.378
is causing
an allodynic response.

01:14.422 --> 01:16.511
Until he can control
what he hears,

01:16.554 --> 01:19.340
every sound
will be accompanied by pain.

01:19.383 --> 01:21.124
- I have to help him.

01:21.168 --> 01:23.213
- Teach him how to focus,
share what you know,

01:23.257 --> 01:26.912
but it will take much practice
on his part,

01:26.956 --> 01:29.089
the same as it did for you,
Kal-El.

01:29.132 --> 01:32.092
[dramatic music]

01:32.135 --> 01:39.099
♪

01:39.142 --> 01:42.537
[sirens wailing, insects
chirping, birds chirping]

01:45.670 --> 01:47.498
[heart beating]

01:47.542 --> 01:50.240
- How long till
the super hearing levels out?

01:50.284 --> 01:53.156
- My father said
he has to adapt on his own.

01:53.200 --> 01:54.723
- How long were you
out of commission for?

01:54.766 --> 01:56.464
- A couple weeks.
- So now, let me guess.

01:56.507 --> 01:58.292
I have to come up
with another BS excuse

01:58.335 --> 02:00.120
as to why
he's not going to school?

02:00.163 --> 02:01.599
- I'll call Principal Balcomb

02:01.643 --> 02:02.905
first thing in the morning,
okay?

02:04.950 --> 02:06.474
You two should get to bed.

02:07.692 --> 02:09.346
- [sighs]

02:09.390 --> 02:11.043
- Jordan.

02:11.087 --> 02:14.046
[somber music]

02:14.090 --> 02:15.831
♪

02:15.874 --> 02:17.702
We'll work on this tomorrow.

02:32.500 --> 02:34.589
Hey, hey.

02:41.248 --> 02:42.901
- He was in so much pain.

02:42.945 --> 02:44.555
- I know, I know.

02:45.991 --> 02:48.559
Once it settles in,
he'll be fine.

02:48.603 --> 02:50.387
Promise.

02:51.736 --> 02:54.696
[ethereal music]

02:54.739 --> 03:01.790
♪

03:03.574 --> 03:06.229
- Listen, I know
we already went over this,

03:06.273 --> 03:08.492
but is there anything
in particular

03:08.536 --> 03:10.233
I should be looking out for?

03:10.277 --> 03:11.974
- If Edge is making
people with powers,

03:12.017 --> 03:13.497
he's not doing it out
in the open,

03:13.541 --> 03:17.414
so kind of just anything
out of the ordinary.

03:17.458 --> 03:20.374
Buildings, machines,
invoices even.

03:20.417 --> 03:22.854
- Okay, and is there
a way to tell

03:22.898 --> 03:24.856
if someone already has powers?

03:24.900 --> 03:26.380
- Not really,

03:26.423 --> 03:28.120
but we do know
that Leslie Larr has powers,

03:28.164 --> 03:30.558
so it's safe to assume
that other people do too.

03:30.601 --> 03:32.255
Lana, I don't want you
doing anything

03:32.299 --> 03:35.084
that makes you
feel even remotely unsafe.

03:35.127 --> 03:36.607
- No, I wanna help.

03:36.651 --> 03:38.479
I'll call you
if I find anything.

03:38.522 --> 03:40.132
- Thanks.
Bye.

03:45.050 --> 03:46.226
- Who's this?

03:46.269 --> 03:48.140
- The real Marcus Bridgewater.

03:48.184 --> 03:50.795
- So the guy from the mines--
- Lied.

03:50.839 --> 03:53.407
Even tried to cover his tracks
by scrubbing all images

03:53.450 --> 03:55.452
of Marcus Bridgewater
from the Internet.

03:55.496 --> 03:56.845
Luckily,
Maxy still has a friend

03:56.888 --> 03:58.281
at Reuters who had a photo.

03:58.325 --> 03:59.456
- So why is he lying
about his identity?

03:59.500 --> 04:00.936
- I don't know.
I mean,

04:00.979 --> 04:02.677
it probably has
something to do with the fact

04:02.720 --> 04:04.592
that he knows
so much about Edge.

04:05.549 --> 04:08.030
- So two people working
for Edge have attacked you,

04:08.073 --> 04:09.901
and both have had powers.

04:09.945 --> 04:12.556
- Yeah.
I'm sure there are others.

04:12.600 --> 04:14.123
- [sighs]
Yeah, which is why I think

04:14.166 --> 04:15.472
we should tell the boys
what's going on.

04:15.516 --> 04:17.126
- Well, that's
a pretty big departure

04:17.169 --> 04:18.997
from not wanting them to know
anything about Superman.

04:19.041 --> 04:21.391
- Well, hindsight, maybe
that wasn't the best choice.

04:21.435 --> 04:22.740
- This feels different.

04:22.784 --> 04:24.264
The whole point
of moving to Smallville

04:24.307 --> 04:25.917
was to give them a shot
at a normal life,

04:25.961 --> 04:28.311
not terrify them.
- I know, I know, but--

04:28.355 --> 04:30.400
- Plus Jordan has the stuff
going on with the hearing,

04:30.444 --> 04:33.664
and Jonathan
hasn't made any friends.

04:33.708 --> 04:34.970
It doesn't feel fair
to give them

04:35.013 --> 04:36.319
one more thing to worry about.

04:36.363 --> 04:37.886
- I think they can handle this.

04:37.929 --> 04:39.366
- I still think that
we need to know more

04:39.409 --> 04:40.367
about what we're dealing with,

04:40.410 --> 04:42.456
and then we can discuss it.

04:42.499 --> 04:45.763
- Okay.
Where are you going?

04:45.807 --> 04:47.591
- To confront
the former Mr. Bridgewater.

04:47.635 --> 04:48.984
Will you stay close by today?

04:49.027 --> 04:50.681
I have a feeling
I'm gonna need your help.

04:50.725 --> 04:52.292
- Yeah.

04:53.989 --> 04:56.992
- Why have you not ID'd
Lane's friend from the mines?

04:57.035 --> 04:58.559
- Believe me, I've looked.

04:58.602 --> 05:00.561
We have no matches
from the security footage.

05:00.604 --> 05:01.779
The guy's a ghost.

05:01.823 --> 05:05.348
- [sighs]
A very well-armed ghost.

05:05.392 --> 05:07.132
Between him, Lane,
and Superman,

05:07.176 --> 05:10.222
how are we supposed to get the
X-Kryptonite out of the mines?

05:10.266 --> 05:13.443
- Maybe we use that
to our advantage,

05:13.487 --> 05:15.967
send out a small shipment,
see who comes for it.

05:16.011 --> 05:18.405
The intel we get in return
could prove invaluable.

05:18.448 --> 05:20.363
- A small fragment only.

05:20.407 --> 05:23.453
And Leslie, no more failures.

05:23.497 --> 05:26.717
[dramatic music]

05:26.761 --> 05:29.416
- Oh, sorry.
I was just about to knock.

05:29.459 --> 05:33.768
♪

05:33.811 --> 05:35.204
- Don't mind her.

05:35.247 --> 05:36.597
Shall we walk?

05:38.033 --> 05:40.992
- So you want me to create
what kind of program?

05:41.036 --> 05:42.385
- A leadership program.

05:42.429 --> 05:44.256
I'm looking
for people with passion

05:44.300 --> 05:47.042
who, like you,
have untapped potential

05:47.085 --> 05:48.913
and are ready
to take that first step.

05:48.957 --> 05:52.395
- First step
towards what exactly?

05:52.439 --> 05:54.397
- Achieving their best selves.

05:54.441 --> 05:55.833
I thought you'd have known that
by now.

05:55.877 --> 05:57.922
- Okay, and how many candidates

05:57.966 --> 05:59.402
were you looking for?

05:59.446 --> 06:01.709
- Why don't we start with five
and go from there?

06:03.450 --> 06:05.495
I'm expecting great things
from you, Lana.

06:14.069 --> 06:17.159
[ethereal music]

06:17.202 --> 06:19.161
- You can do this.

06:19.204 --> 06:20.510
- It hurts.

06:20.554 --> 06:21.642
- I know, but you're gonna have

06:21.685 --> 06:23.557
to work through it, okay?

06:23.600 --> 06:25.733
One sound at a time.
Come on.

06:31.086 --> 06:32.783
- [sighs]

06:37.875 --> 06:40.051
[loud rumbling]

06:40.095 --> 06:42.227
[rumbling dying down]

06:45.492 --> 06:48.495
[piercing hiss]

06:52.455 --> 06:55.458
[chiming splashes]

06:55.502 --> 06:59.462
[rumbling and traffic]

07:01.986 --> 07:03.858
I can't do it.
I'm sorry.

07:06.774 --> 07:08.471
- Jordan.
Jordan.

07:08.515 --> 07:10.691
- We'll just try it tomorrow
or something.

07:10.734 --> 07:13.389
- Audio is fully operational.

07:13.433 --> 07:15.347
It's good to be back, sir.

07:15.391 --> 07:17.132
- You're still only at 30%.

07:17.175 --> 07:19.177
- Perhaps you'll consider that
next time

07:19.221 --> 07:21.397
before crushing me
to smithereens.

07:22.093 --> 07:23.225
[knocking]

07:23.268 --> 07:26.228
[dramatic music]

07:26.271 --> 07:33.322
♪

07:41.939 --> 07:43.332
- Lois Lane.

07:43.375 --> 07:46.509
- Hello, guy who is
not Marcus Bridgewater.

07:47.423 --> 07:49.425
- How about you come inside,
and we talk about it?

07:49.469 --> 07:50.600
- Yeah, that's a hard pass

07:50.644 --> 07:52.689
on me entering
your creeper mobile.

07:52.733 --> 07:55.387
- That's unfair
and pretty hurtful.

07:56.780 --> 07:58.478
- Meet me at Victoria May's
in an hour.

07:58.521 --> 07:59.957
And get ready
to tell the truth.

08:00.001 --> 08:02.046
Otherwise, this little team-up
of ours is done.

08:03.047 --> 08:06.007
[tense music]

08:06.050 --> 08:08.618
♪

08:08.662 --> 08:10.185
[engine starts]

08:17.018 --> 08:18.759
- What are you thinking about
this early?

08:18.802 --> 08:20.064
- [laughs]

08:20.108 --> 08:21.892
Same thing as last night.

08:25.896 --> 08:28.420
- You are playing with fire.

08:29.247 --> 08:31.598
- Ugh, childhood ruined.
Therapy needed.

08:31.641 --> 08:32.686
Thanks a lot, Mom and Dad.

08:32.729 --> 08:33.861
- [sighs]
Hey, Nat-Bug.

08:33.904 --> 08:35.384
- Look, I'm not gonna be tardy

08:35.427 --> 08:36.820
just because you two
can't stop being disgusting.

08:36.864 --> 08:38.561
- Whoa, it's not disgusting.

08:38.605 --> 08:40.302
No, this is
a loving display of--

08:40.345 --> 08:41.956
- Affection.
Yeah, I know.

08:41.999 --> 08:43.566
You know why I know?

08:43.610 --> 08:44.785
Because you two are
the most affectionate people

08:44.828 --> 08:45.873
I've ever seen in my life.

08:45.916 --> 08:47.614
[both laughing]

08:47.657 --> 08:50.399
[explosions]

08:50.442 --> 08:53.402
[ominous music]

08:53.445 --> 08:56.274
♪

08:56.318 --> 08:59.277
[crowd screaming]

08:59.321 --> 09:04.021
♪

09:04.065 --> 09:06.328
- What's Superman doing?

09:06.371 --> 09:07.764
- And who's he with?

09:07.808 --> 09:13.857
♪

09:13.901 --> 09:16.164
[crowd screaming]

09:18.993 --> 09:22.039
[crowd screaming]

09:27.131 --> 09:28.219
- Oh, my God.

09:28.263 --> 09:30.395
- [screaming]

09:30.439 --> 09:33.398
[emotional music]

09:33.442 --> 09:40.492
♪

09:44.758 --> 09:47.717
[clock ticking]

09:47.761 --> 09:50.720
[ethereal music]

09:50.764 --> 09:57.814
♪

10:08.782 --> 10:10.261
- [sighs]

10:15.484 --> 10:18.443
[loud clock ticking, rumbling,
birds chirping]

10:18.487 --> 10:21.533
[indistinct chatter]

10:23.579 --> 10:26.626
[clock chimes]
[ears ringing]

10:27.191 --> 10:29.629
[radio murmurs]

10:29.672 --> 10:31.848
[car beeping]

10:31.892 --> 10:34.851
[indistinct chatter]

10:34.895 --> 10:37.854
[car beeping, baby laughing]

10:37.898 --> 10:39.377
[horn honking]

10:39.421 --> 10:42.467
[heavy breathing]

10:46.950 --> 10:48.778
[bell rings]

10:53.740 --> 10:55.742
- Yo, Cushing, hey.

10:55.785 --> 10:57.395
Didn't--I didn't see you
at lunch today.

10:57.439 --> 10:59.397
Is everything all right?

10:59.441 --> 11:00.964
- Maybe you should tell me.

11:01.008 --> 11:03.097
Why isn't Jordan
at school today?

11:03.140 --> 11:05.055
- Uh, I mean, he's not
really feeling well.

11:05.577 --> 11:06.970
- Right.

11:07.014 --> 11:08.363
- Hey, what--
hold on, hold on, hold on.

11:08.406 --> 11:10.626
What's going on?
- You're lying to me.

11:10.670 --> 11:12.628
- About Jordan being sick?

11:12.672 --> 11:14.674
- You know what happened
last night with Tag,

11:14.717 --> 11:16.327
and you're acting as though
Jordan not coming to school

11:16.371 --> 11:17.894
is--kinda weird.

11:17.938 --> 11:20.114
- Well, yeah, Sarah, Sarah,
hey, hey, look.

11:20.157 --> 11:22.159
I know what happened
with Tag, okay?

11:22.203 --> 11:23.770
And I'm sorry,
it's really messed up,

11:23.813 --> 11:25.728
but Jordan had nothing
to do with that.

11:27.208 --> 11:28.557
- That's not what Tag said.

11:28.600 --> 11:30.211
- What?
'Cause of some stupid video?

11:30.254 --> 11:31.995
Did you even watch it?

11:32.039 --> 11:34.476
Seriously, look, I mean,
there's absolutely no way

11:34.519 --> 11:36.391
that Jordan gave Tag powers
or whatever.

11:36.434 --> 11:37.871
And also, truth be told,

11:37.914 --> 11:39.742
the reason that Jordan's
not at school

11:39.786 --> 11:42.136
is because Tag jumped him
the other day.

11:42.179 --> 11:44.268
And it totally messed him up,

11:44.312 --> 11:47.141
and now he's having
these terrible headaches.

11:47.184 --> 11:48.925
- That's why he had bruises
on his face.

11:50.100 --> 11:51.885
Why didn't he just tell me?
- I don't know.

11:51.928 --> 11:53.582
I guess he didn't want you
to worry.

11:55.802 --> 11:57.847
See?
He's not such a bad guy.

11:57.891 --> 11:58.848
- Yeah.

11:58.892 --> 12:00.763
- And also,

12:00.807 --> 12:02.330
yeah, I broke my wrist.

12:02.373 --> 12:03.940
Thanks for asking.
It really sucks.

12:05.159 --> 12:06.900
- Jonathan.

12:06.943 --> 12:08.640
[somber music]

12:08.684 --> 12:10.468
Jonathan!

12:10.512 --> 12:12.993
♪

12:13.036 --> 12:14.603
[groans]

12:14.646 --> 12:16.344
- I gotta say,
I don't love the idea

12:16.387 --> 12:17.780
of leaving you alone with him.

12:17.824 --> 12:20.043
- Well, get used to it,
'cause he's here.

12:20.087 --> 12:21.610
- And what exactly
am I looking for?

12:21.653 --> 12:22.916
- You'll know it
when you see it.

12:22.959 --> 12:24.700
Here, wish me luck.

12:24.744 --> 12:26.789
- Good luck.

12:26.833 --> 12:29.792
[mysterious music]

12:29.836 --> 12:35.102
♪

12:35.145 --> 12:36.930
[bell dings]

12:42.065 --> 12:44.328
- I ordered you
a trenté green tea

12:44.372 --> 12:45.721
with a splash of almond milk.

12:47.505 --> 12:49.812
It's what you got last time.

12:49.856 --> 12:51.945
- I think it's time
we moved past favorite drinks

12:51.988 --> 12:54.121
and actually got to know
each other.

12:54.164 --> 12:55.252
- Absolutely.

12:55.296 --> 12:56.819
- Great.
I'll go first.

12:56.863 --> 12:57.994
You've been lying to me
ever since we first met.

12:58.038 --> 12:59.169
- You're wrong about that.

12:59.213 --> 13:00.823
I mean, obviously

13:00.867 --> 13:02.912
not the name part,

13:02.956 --> 13:04.348
but everything else is true.

13:04.392 --> 13:05.697
- Then who are you?

13:05.741 --> 13:07.090
- It's complicated.

13:07.134 --> 13:08.918
- Then you better start
boiling it down.

13:14.576 --> 13:16.273
- Welcome back, Captain.

13:16.317 --> 13:18.580
How was your conversation
with Lois Lane?

13:22.627 --> 13:24.064
Captain Luthor?

13:24.107 --> 13:26.544
[dramatic music]

13:26.588 --> 13:28.895
- Telling you who I am
will only confuse things.

13:28.938 --> 13:30.200
What's important
is you understand

13:30.244 --> 13:31.636
what Edge is really planning.

13:31.680 --> 13:33.029
- I know he's making people
with powers.

13:33.073 --> 13:34.683
- Not people.
An army.

13:34.726 --> 13:37.164
- An army to do what?
- Take over the world.

13:37.207 --> 13:39.122
Metropolis will be
the first city to fall.

13:39.166 --> 13:40.950
- You seem awfully sureof that.

13:40.994 --> 13:42.212
- Because it's the truth.

13:42.256 --> 13:43.866
- And why should I believe you?

13:43.910 --> 13:46.869
[cell phone ringing]

13:46.913 --> 13:53.093
♪

13:53.136 --> 13:54.790
Hey.

13:54.834 --> 13:56.183
- Okay, so I have
a contact in shipping

13:56.226 --> 13:57.619
at Edge's mines--

13:57.662 --> 13:59.229
Well, I mean,
not really a contact,

13:59.273 --> 14:00.840
more like an ex
who really never got over me.

14:00.883 --> 14:02.319
- Chrissy.

14:02.363 --> 14:03.799
- Edge is about
to send a shipment out.

14:03.843 --> 14:06.019
Do you think
it's X-Kryptonite?

14:06.062 --> 14:09.022
- Only one way to find out.
Thanks, boss.

14:10.066 --> 14:11.285
We'll have to pick this up
some other time.

14:11.328 --> 14:12.764
Something came up.

14:12.808 --> 14:14.070
- Lois, this is serious.

14:14.114 --> 14:15.376
I need to speak with Superman.

14:15.419 --> 14:16.377
- Maybe when we're on

14:16.420 --> 14:17.857
a first-name basis.

14:21.948 --> 14:23.775
[bell dings]

14:25.212 --> 14:26.648
- [sighs]

14:26.691 --> 14:28.824
[whooshing]
- Well, that was fast.

14:28.868 --> 14:31.087
- Chrissy called.
Looks like Edge is on the move.

14:31.131 --> 14:32.610
Any luck with the RV?
- [scoffs]

14:32.654 --> 14:34.612
You were right about knowing it
when I found it.

14:34.656 --> 14:37.006
- It seems we have a problem.

14:37.050 --> 14:39.791
- [sighs]
Lois will come around.

14:39.835 --> 14:42.055
- I was referring
to the intruder.

14:42.925 --> 14:45.188
- Intruder?
In here?

14:45.232 --> 14:47.147
- Yes, Captain.
I managed to capture

14:47.190 --> 14:48.931
an image
in front of the monitors.

14:51.238 --> 14:53.283
- [sighs]
That's her husband.

14:53.327 --> 14:54.763
- Is he a threat?

14:54.806 --> 14:56.721
- No.
He's not important.

14:56.765 --> 14:59.376
- There's also been
a development at the mines.

14:59.420 --> 15:01.944
Satellite imaging is showing
increased activity.

15:01.988 --> 15:03.815
- That's what her call
was about.

15:05.295 --> 15:06.557
Pull it up.

15:06.601 --> 15:09.647
- [murmuring]
[phone ringing]

15:14.783 --> 15:16.393
Emily.
[laughs]

15:16.437 --> 15:18.874
Hi.
Take a seat.

15:18.918 --> 15:20.658
What are you doing here?

15:20.702 --> 15:22.878
- Well, um,
I was just told

15:22.922 --> 15:24.358
that you were the one
I'm supposed to talk to

15:24.401 --> 15:27.013
about the Young
Executive Program.

15:27.056 --> 15:28.362
- Yes.

15:28.405 --> 15:30.364
Yeah,
I'm actually just starting

15:30.407 --> 15:31.974
to get into all that now.

15:32.018 --> 15:33.889
- Well, listen, I, uh, I know

15:33.933 --> 15:35.586
I've been out of the workforce
for a while,

15:35.630 --> 15:37.675
but you know,
we couldn't afford childcare,

15:37.719 --> 15:39.634
and now that Avery's
in high school--

15:39.677 --> 15:41.114
- Oh, no, no, no.

15:41.157 --> 15:42.680
You do not need to defend
being a mother to me.

15:42.724 --> 15:45.988
- Good, because
I really want this, Lana.

15:46.032 --> 15:48.599
This is a chance for me to make
a better life for my family,

15:48.643 --> 15:49.992
just like what you're doing.

15:50.036 --> 15:51.776
- There are tradeoffs.

15:51.820 --> 15:54.083
I mean, there are things
you might not be aware of.

15:54.127 --> 15:56.738
- Oh, you don't have to pretend
like this job isn't a big deal.

15:56.781 --> 15:58.609
It's obvious.

15:58.653 --> 16:02.135
I'm just, um, asking for
someone to take a chance on me

16:02.178 --> 16:05.007
like they did with you.

16:05.051 --> 16:06.617
- I appreciate that.

16:11.405 --> 16:13.973
[sighs]
Let me see what I can do,

16:14.016 --> 16:15.496
but no promises.

16:15.539 --> 16:17.846
- Thank you, Lana.
Thank you so much.

16:17.889 --> 16:19.891
- Of course.

16:22.285 --> 16:23.852
Nice to see you.

16:23.895 --> 16:25.462
- Good to see you.

16:25.506 --> 16:27.203
- Bye.

16:30.424 --> 16:32.121
- Could he actually be
Lex Luthor?

16:32.165 --> 16:34.036
- I don't know,
but with everything we know

16:34.080 --> 16:36.125
about the multiverse now,
I'd say anything's possible.

16:36.169 --> 16:37.648
- [sighs]
Like what?

16:37.692 --> 16:39.955
He's related to Lex somehow?

16:39.999 --> 16:41.478
Maybe a son
we don't know about?

16:41.522 --> 16:42.914
- Well, he said
he worked for LuthorCorps.

16:42.958 --> 16:44.351
That can't just be
a coincidence.

16:44.394 --> 16:45.830
- Yeah.

16:45.874 --> 16:47.310
And Lex wouldn't be
the first public figure

16:47.354 --> 16:49.051
trying to keep his family
hidden from the world.

16:49.095 --> 16:50.226
- I'll have Chrissy
look into it.

16:50.270 --> 16:52.098
Are they still up ahead?

16:52.141 --> 16:54.622
- Yeah.
About two miles up.

16:54.665 --> 16:57.016
It looks like
they've got an escort.

16:57.059 --> 16:58.887
There's a panel van with
four guys with guns inside

16:58.930 --> 17:00.584
a couple cars back.

17:00.628 --> 17:02.282
- That seems on brand for Edge.

17:02.325 --> 17:04.197
- What do you wanna do?
- Just keep following.

17:04.240 --> 17:06.851
I wanna see where they're
taking the X-Kryptonite.

17:06.895 --> 17:09.724
- I don't think
that's gonna happen.

17:11.726 --> 17:13.467
- What is it?

17:13.510 --> 17:14.990
- I'm definitely starting
to think

17:15.034 --> 17:16.731
your new friend is a Luthor.

17:24.869 --> 17:26.697
[dramatic music]

17:26.741 --> 17:28.525
- Hey, guys, we got someone
in the road up here.

17:28.569 --> 17:29.874
Be ready.

17:29.918 --> 17:31.528
♪

17:31.572 --> 17:33.835
- Locked and loaded, boys.
It's go time.

17:36.968 --> 17:39.449
- [sighs] Things are gonna get
ugly if I don't do something.

17:39.493 --> 17:40.842
[whooshing]

17:50.678 --> 17:53.333
- Out of the truck!
Get out of the truck!

17:55.161 --> 17:56.945
Turn around.
Get on your knees.

17:59.121 --> 18:00.862
[whooshing]

18:02.037 --> 18:04.692
[whooshing]
- What the hell?

18:04.735 --> 18:07.782
[cell phone ringing]

18:10.480 --> 18:12.047
- We have a problem.

18:16.225 --> 18:17.313
- Don't move.

18:24.755 --> 18:27.802
[beeping]

18:30.848 --> 18:32.807
- What are you doing?

18:32.850 --> 18:34.287
- I assume the same thing
you are.

18:37.377 --> 18:39.161
- No, we were following
the truck

18:39.205 --> 18:40.989
hoping to find out
where it was headed,

18:41.032 --> 18:42.382
which, now, we'll never know

18:42.425 --> 18:45.036
since you decided
to go full-on Rambo!

18:48.388 --> 18:50.172
- I couldn't risk letting this
get where it was going.

18:50.216 --> 18:52.566
- 'Cause that's what Edge
is gonna use to build his army?

18:52.609 --> 18:53.697
- So you believe me now?

18:53.741 --> 18:55.569
- Enough games.

18:55.612 --> 18:58.049
Tell us what you know.

18:58.093 --> 19:00.356
- Fine.
Follow me.

19:08.103 --> 19:09.757
- You sure showed that locker.

19:09.800 --> 19:11.106
- Yeah, yeah.

19:11.150 --> 19:13.064
Had it coming.

19:13.108 --> 19:14.457
[ethereal music]

19:14.501 --> 19:16.372
Uh, hi.

19:16.416 --> 19:19.201
- If the zipper gets stuck,
maybe you should try

19:19.245 --> 19:21.116
talking to it first.
[laughs]

19:21.160 --> 19:24.163
Nothing good
ever comes from anger.

19:24.206 --> 19:25.860
- Right, yeah, yeah,
sure, yeah.

19:25.903 --> 19:27.818
I mean, I'm--I'm--

19:27.862 --> 19:29.603
I'm not gonna, like, talk
to my backpack.

19:29.646 --> 19:31.344
That's--that's weird.

19:31.387 --> 19:33.041
- Right.

19:33.084 --> 19:35.304
I'll see you around, new guy.

19:35.348 --> 19:38.351
♪

19:38.394 --> 19:40.179
- No, no, no, no, no.

19:40.222 --> 19:43.094
Jonathan, no.
Not Tegan Wickhem.

19:43.138 --> 19:44.792
She's way out of your league.

19:44.835 --> 19:47.055
- That's a bit presumptuous,

19:47.098 --> 19:49.797
and besides, how do you know
what my league is?

19:49.840 --> 19:52.016
- I know it's not her.

19:54.280 --> 19:56.847
Look, I came over here
to apologize.

19:56.891 --> 19:58.458
I didn't mean
to accuse you of lying

19:58.501 --> 20:01.025
or Jordan of...

20:01.069 --> 20:02.549
I don't know.

20:02.592 --> 20:04.333
- That's--it's cool.

20:04.377 --> 20:05.421
- No, it's not.

20:05.465 --> 20:07.162
I'm really worried about Tag.

20:07.206 --> 20:08.946
He's my friend,

20:08.990 --> 20:10.426
and you and Jordan
are the only people

20:10.470 --> 20:12.689
who know
what really happened, so...

20:12.733 --> 20:16.302
- Yeah, I know, it's a lot
keeping a secret like that.

20:16.345 --> 20:18.042
I know.

20:21.481 --> 20:22.873
- [sighs]

20:22.917 --> 20:26.399
[low rumbling, scraping]

20:26.442 --> 20:29.402
[dog barking, traffic]

20:29.445 --> 20:32.405
[beeping]

20:32.448 --> 20:34.320
[rumbling]

20:34.363 --> 20:37.105
[sound stops]
[heavy breathing]

20:48.334 --> 20:51.293
[warm music]

20:51.337 --> 20:53.469
♪

20:53.513 --> 20:56.472
[radio buzzing,
indistinct chatter]

20:56.516 --> 20:59.475
[crowd cheering]

20:59.519 --> 21:02.304
- Not being the only one
who knows about this helps.

21:02.348 --> 21:04.654
I guess I'm pretty lucky
to have you.

21:04.698 --> 21:06.569
- I guess I've been in
Smallville long enough to know

21:06.613 --> 21:08.832
that you're different
than everyone else.

21:08.876 --> 21:11.661
- Really?
How so?

21:11.705 --> 21:13.402
- Mm.

21:13.446 --> 21:16.666
I don't know, just--
just, like, more real I guess.

21:16.710 --> 21:18.625
I can tell you hold
a lot of stuff inside,

21:18.668 --> 21:22.106
and I get that.
I get how hard that can be,

21:22.150 --> 21:24.457
so I guess--
I guess what I'm saying is

21:24.500 --> 21:27.242
if you ever need someone
to share that with,

21:27.286 --> 21:29.244
I'm always here.

21:29.288 --> 21:31.333
- Wow, you're kind of in a
better league than I thought.

21:31.377 --> 21:34.423
[ears ringing]

21:47.958 --> 21:50.657
- If Edge is using
X-Kryptonite to build an army,

21:50.700 --> 21:53.616
why would he send
such a small shipment?

21:53.660 --> 21:55.488
- Probably wanted to see
who'd come for it.

21:55.531 --> 21:58.404
- Well, now that he knows,
what's his next move?

21:58.447 --> 22:00.406
- It's hard to say,
but we need to be ready.

22:00.449 --> 22:01.842
- Ready how?

22:01.885 --> 22:03.017
- It's what I was trying
to tell you earlier.

22:03.060 --> 22:05.062
- You wanna meet Superman.

22:05.106 --> 22:06.977
- It's the only way
to stop this.

22:07.021 --> 22:09.110
- Dad, wake up!
Dad!

22:09.153 --> 22:10.720
Dad, wake up.
Dad.

22:10.764 --> 22:11.982
- Hmm?
Hmm?

22:12.026 --> 22:14.376
Hey, where's your mom?

22:14.420 --> 22:16.378
[somber music]

22:16.422 --> 22:18.641
- Coming to you live
from Downtown Metropolis,

22:18.685 --> 22:20.643
reporting on the scene
is Lois Lane.

22:20.687 --> 22:21.818
♪

22:21.862 --> 22:23.342
- You want answers?

22:23.385 --> 22:24.952
I'm willing to tell
Superman everything.

22:24.995 --> 22:26.345
- I'm not in the habit

22:26.388 --> 22:27.911
of just connecting him
with people.

22:27.955 --> 22:29.348
- I'm thinking
the possible end of the world

22:29.391 --> 22:31.785
might warrant an exception.
- Okay.

22:31.828 --> 22:35.484
But I want something from you.
That.

22:36.572 --> 22:38.922
The Kryptonians want you to
think they're indestructible.

22:38.966 --> 22:40.881
They're not.
They have a weakness.

22:40.924 --> 22:43.492
It is a rock from their home
planet called Kryptonite.

22:43.536 --> 22:46.147
Find it
so that we can defeat them.

22:46.190 --> 22:47.714
- I told her not to do this.

22:47.757 --> 22:48.889
- And we must defeat them

22:48.932 --> 22:50.978
if we are to save humanity.

22:52.066 --> 22:54.111
For that is what separates us
from them:

22:54.155 --> 22:56.287
our humanity.

22:56.331 --> 22:57.550
- Mom!

23:00.466 --> 23:01.684
- Okay.

23:04.078 --> 23:06.210
But I need to know
one thing first.

23:08.430 --> 23:09.953
Do you trust him?

23:12.303 --> 23:14.131
- With my life.

23:15.785 --> 23:18.266
I love you both.

23:18.309 --> 23:19.920
[screams]

23:28.581 --> 23:30.191
- I thought you'd say that.

23:33.237 --> 23:35.239
Set up the meet.

23:44.640 --> 23:46.947
[ethereal music]

23:46.990 --> 23:48.601
- All right,
I'm gonna meet Chrissy,

23:48.644 --> 23:50.385
see if I can establish
any connection

23:50.429 --> 23:51.778
between our guy and Lex.

23:51.821 --> 23:54.302
- Yeah, I guess it's still
our only lead.

23:54.345 --> 23:56.043
- Maybe not.
You said the voice in the RV

23:56.086 --> 23:57.087
called him Captain.

23:57.131 --> 23:58.785
- Right, so he's military.

23:58.828 --> 24:00.221
- Which is why I want you
to take that

24:00.264 --> 24:01.570
to the DOD for processing.

24:01.614 --> 24:03.616
- [laughs]

24:03.659 --> 24:04.878
- What?

24:04.921 --> 24:07.271
- Nothing.
Just, it has his prints.

24:07.315 --> 24:09.143
You know,
you're really good at this.

24:09.186 --> 24:10.753
- You better get moving,
Superman.

24:10.797 --> 24:13.234
We don't have much time
before your meeting.

24:14.191 --> 24:15.584
- All right.

24:15.628 --> 24:16.933
[sighs]

24:16.977 --> 24:24.027
♪

24:30.120 --> 24:32.993
- Do you believe Kal-El
will come?

24:33.036 --> 24:34.211
- I do.

24:35.517 --> 24:36.910
And we need to be ready.

24:37.911 --> 24:40.870
[dramatic synth music]

24:40.914 --> 24:47.877
♪

25:38.624 --> 25:40.408
- [grunts]

26:21.841 --> 26:24.887
[electricity crackling]
[machinery whirring]

26:34.114 --> 26:36.595
- It's smaller than I imagined.

26:36.638 --> 26:38.640
- I couldn't have done it
without you, Nat-Bug.

26:48.084 --> 26:50.521
- So I can be out there with
you when you're kicking ass.

26:52.785 --> 26:55.222
You really think you could take
one of them out?

26:56.702 --> 26:59.139
- Only one way
to know for sure.

27:18.027 --> 27:20.247
- Hey.

27:20.290 --> 27:21.640
- What were you talking
to Sarah about earlier?

27:21.683 --> 27:24.425
- What are you--
Are you spying on me?

27:25.556 --> 27:26.645
[scoffs]
Wow.

27:27.689 --> 27:28.821
- Just answer the question.

27:28.864 --> 27:30.257
- Uh, I was talking to her

27:30.300 --> 27:31.737
like a normal human being.

27:31.780 --> 27:33.129
- That's not
what it sounded like.

27:33.173 --> 27:34.870
- Are you being serious
right now?

27:34.914 --> 27:36.219
I've been covering your ass
all day,

27:36.263 --> 27:37.960
and now what?

27:38.004 --> 27:40.310
Now you think I'm trying to
move in on your not-girlfriend?

27:40.354 --> 27:43.052
- That's not a denial.
- Wow, I have had your back

27:43.096 --> 27:46.577
every time someone
has called you dumb or weird

27:46.621 --> 27:49.102
or stupid or awkward.
[ears ringing]

27:49.145 --> 27:51.278
I never believed any of it!

27:51.321 --> 27:53.628
I never believed any of it
because it's not true.

27:53.672 --> 27:55.761
You're just a terrible person!

27:55.804 --> 27:57.588
Don't ever spy on me again!

27:57.632 --> 27:59.721
[dramatic music]

27:59.765 --> 28:02.898
[echoing thump]
- [grunts]

28:06.206 --> 28:07.729
- Impressive bunch
you've assembled.

28:07.773 --> 28:09.252
- Well, there's no shortage

28:09.296 --> 28:10.689
of good people in Smallville.

28:12.125 --> 28:13.779
- And yet, one spot remains.

28:13.822 --> 28:15.737
- One spot.

28:15.781 --> 28:18.740
Just getting through
the last of the résumés.

28:18.784 --> 28:20.481
- Is that it,

28:20.524 --> 28:22.048
or is there something
you're not telling me?

28:22.091 --> 28:25.268
- Um, I don't understand.

28:25.312 --> 28:26.661
- I just thought
perhaps you were hoping

28:26.705 --> 28:28.881
I'd select someone
a little closer to home.

28:28.924 --> 28:30.273
- You mean Kyle.

28:30.317 --> 28:31.971
- I believe he'd be
more than interested.

28:32.014 --> 28:33.537
- Of course.[laughs]

28:33.581 --> 28:35.714
But he's the chief
of the fire department.

28:35.757 --> 28:38.542
- Arrangements could be made.
- Oh, I'm sure,

28:38.586 --> 28:41.241
and it would be
an amazing opportunity,

28:41.284 --> 28:44.026
but it would a lot to juggle
with our girls.

28:44.070 --> 28:45.158
- I understand,

28:45.201 --> 28:47.508
but we are short on time.

28:47.551 --> 28:49.684
I look forward to hearing
your decision.

28:51.425 --> 28:54.471
- Luthor's biographer says
there is no way he has a son.

28:56.038 --> 28:58.214
- Maybe a cousin
or distant relative?

28:58.258 --> 29:00.129
- She walked me
through every branch

29:00.173 --> 29:01.478
of the Luthor family tree.

29:01.522 --> 29:03.654
Our guy is
definitely not on it.

29:04.612 --> 29:05.918
- [sighs]

29:08.834 --> 29:11.227
[whooshes]

29:17.625 --> 29:20.454
- Interesting place for a meet.

29:20.497 --> 29:22.238
- I'm a builder.

29:22.282 --> 29:24.632
Always felt comfortable
in places like this...

29:26.242 --> 29:28.418
Surrounded by scraps and parts.

29:29.506 --> 29:32.031
- Building's
a noble profession.

29:32.074 --> 29:34.947
- Been a while since
anyone's paid me to do it.

29:34.990 --> 29:37.558
- Any chance one
of those people was Lex Luthor?

29:39.038 --> 29:40.735
- It was a different life.

29:41.431 --> 29:42.998
- Why are we really here?

29:44.347 --> 29:47.089
- Because the world's about to
be destroyed unless I save it.

29:49.178 --> 29:51.398
[cell phone ringing]

29:51.441 --> 29:52.921
- It's the DOD.

29:52.965 --> 29:54.662
Hey, Rosetti, what'd you find?

29:54.705 --> 29:57.230
- You say this guy's been
creeping around Smallville?

29:57.273 --> 29:59.710
- And how exactly are you
planning on saving the world?

29:59.754 --> 30:01.756
- By eliminating the threat.

30:01.800 --> 30:03.932
- And you think that threat
is Morgan Edge?

30:03.976 --> 30:05.673
- Edge is involved,

30:05.716 --> 30:08.719
but he won't be
the main source of destruction.

30:08.763 --> 30:09.938
- Then who will it be?

30:15.378 --> 30:17.076
- The thing is,
the prints you had us pull

30:17.119 --> 30:18.773
are from a guy who died
six years ago,

30:18.817 --> 30:22.472
and his name's not Luthor,
it's John Henry Irons.

30:24.561 --> 30:26.215
- Give me your keys.
I need your car.

30:31.830 --> 30:33.135
- You're the Stranger.

30:33.179 --> 30:35.311
[whooshes]
[grunts]

30:38.010 --> 30:40.490
- I had a feeling
you might try that.

30:41.535 --> 30:43.842
So I set these solar flares

30:43.885 --> 30:45.147
to a motion detector.

30:45.191 --> 30:46.409
- Why are you doing this?

30:46.453 --> 30:48.281
- Like I said,

30:48.324 --> 30:51.023
I'm here to save the world.

30:51.066 --> 30:53.895
You see, Kal-El,
you're not the Man of Steel.

30:57.072 --> 30:58.552
I am.

31:02.164 --> 31:03.470
- [grunts]

31:03.513 --> 31:06.299
[dramatic music]

31:06.342 --> 31:09.606
♪

31:09.650 --> 31:11.565
- [grunts]

31:12.044 --> 31:13.872
- That looked like it hurt.

31:16.744 --> 31:19.007
[ears ringing]

31:19.051 --> 31:21.270
- [heavy breathing]

31:21.314 --> 31:25.361
This hammer
harnesses kinetic energy.

31:25.405 --> 31:27.537
The further it travels,

31:27.581 --> 31:29.365
the more energy it creates.

31:30.366 --> 31:34.501
From 20 feet, it can stop
a car in its tracks.

31:34.544 --> 31:36.633
30, a truck.

31:36.677 --> 31:39.941
From 60, it can destroy a tank.

31:39.985 --> 31:41.900
Anything beyond that

31:41.943 --> 31:45.425
rivals a blow from Superman.

31:49.864 --> 31:51.822
- [screams]

32:00.092 --> 32:01.571
- Miss Larr?

32:01.615 --> 32:04.313
- Superman's gonna be busy
for a while.

32:04.357 --> 32:06.272
Send the shipment.

32:08.448 --> 32:10.232
[ears ringing]

32:10.276 --> 32:12.495
- [screaming]

32:13.844 --> 32:15.411
- Is that all you have,
Kal-El?

32:15.455 --> 32:17.022
[clanging]

32:17.065 --> 32:18.806
- Hey.
Jordan, Jordan, Jordan, hey.

32:18.849 --> 32:20.503
- I think someone's trying
to kill Dad.

32:20.547 --> 32:22.244
- What?
Where?

32:22.288 --> 32:25.813
- Clark, his name
is John Henry Irons!

32:25.856 --> 32:28.163
I think he's the Stranger!

32:28.207 --> 32:29.556
Clark!

32:32.515 --> 32:34.039
- Okay, you're gonna have
to go faster, all right?

32:34.082 --> 32:35.562
- Jordan, I've only driven
Mom's car before!

32:35.605 --> 32:36.911
Please just tell me
which way to go.

32:36.955 --> 32:38.695
- It's so loud.

32:38.739 --> 32:40.175
- Well, whenever you were
listening to me and Sarah

32:40.219 --> 32:41.350
at school earlier,
whenever you heard us,

32:41.394 --> 32:42.612
please do that.Please.

32:42.656 --> 32:44.223
- [heavy breathing]

32:44.266 --> 32:46.312
- Jordan, please focus.Please.

32:47.356 --> 32:49.010
- You're wrong about me.

32:49.054 --> 32:51.012
- That way!
That way, that way, that way!

32:58.889 --> 33:01.196
- This hero act of yours

33:01.240 --> 33:03.242
is all propaganda,

33:03.285 --> 33:06.245
a way to soften the masses
before you turn on them.

33:08.203 --> 33:10.989
I made a promise
to kill you once.

33:12.686 --> 33:15.080
I wasn't able to keep
that promise on my Earth.

33:16.690 --> 33:18.431
But I will here.

33:19.040 --> 33:21.695
[both screaming]

33:33.098 --> 33:34.099
- Lights...
- What?

33:34.142 --> 33:35.970
- The lights.

33:41.193 --> 33:44.239
- [grunting]

34:08.002 --> 34:11.049
- [heavy breathing]

34:19.013 --> 34:20.406
- Stop!

34:22.408 --> 34:24.236
It's over.

34:24.279 --> 34:25.585
It's over.

34:27.282 --> 34:30.329
- [coughing]

34:43.646 --> 34:45.605
- So this guy came back from
the dead to try and kill you?

34:45.648 --> 34:47.824
- Wouldn't be the first time.

34:47.868 --> 34:49.348
- Want Trask to take
a run at him?

34:49.391 --> 34:50.523
Try and loosen him up?

34:50.566 --> 34:52.307
- Nobody talks to him

34:52.351 --> 34:54.744
until General Lane gets here
in the morning.

34:54.788 --> 34:56.920
And when he does,

34:56.964 --> 34:59.097
I'm going in first.

35:05.277 --> 35:07.409
[doorbell ringing]

35:07.453 --> 35:09.977
- I'll get it.
- Thanks, sweets.

35:10.717 --> 35:13.111
- Hey, Sophie, hi.
- My mom's right in here.

35:16.505 --> 35:18.072
- Hey, Emily.

35:18.116 --> 35:19.421
- I got the job.

35:19.465 --> 35:21.510
Morgan Edge called me himself.

35:21.554 --> 35:23.077
I am starting tomorrow.

35:23.121 --> 35:24.557
- Emily, I didn't--

35:24.600 --> 35:25.688
- Oh, no,
you don't have to take credit.

35:25.732 --> 35:27.255
I totally know it was you.

35:27.299 --> 35:29.039
Mr. Edge even said
seeing you and I together

35:29.083 --> 35:30.693
is what convinced him
to choose me.

35:30.737 --> 35:32.260
[laughs]

35:32.304 --> 35:34.262
Well, listen, Avery and Duc
are in the car.

35:34.306 --> 35:36.656
I just wanted to come by
and say thank you.

35:36.699 --> 35:40.181
Thank you so much.
You have changed my life, Lana.

35:40.225 --> 35:41.487
[laughs]

35:41.530 --> 35:43.271
[door clicks open]
- [sighs]

35:43.315 --> 35:44.403
[door clicks shut]

35:50.452 --> 35:52.193
- This better be good news.

35:52.237 --> 35:54.587
- The X-Kryptonite just arrived
at the facility.

35:54.630 --> 35:56.241
Everything's ready
to move forward.

35:57.807 --> 35:59.069
- So your plan worked.

35:59.113 --> 36:00.854
- Even better
than I anticipated.

36:00.897 --> 36:02.551
- Lucky you.

36:03.552 --> 36:05.511
- Were you able
to find enough Subjekts?

36:05.554 --> 36:09.254
- Yes, but there's no guarantee
they'll be receptive hosts.

36:09.297 --> 36:10.690
You're still the only one

36:10.733 --> 36:12.474
who hasn't shown
any signs of rejection.

36:13.258 --> 36:15.869
- I guess you have to break
a few eggs to make an omelet.

36:15.912 --> 36:17.305
- Indeed.

36:19.089 --> 36:20.830
And now we have our eggs.

36:25.531 --> 36:28.403
- DOD has John Irons
on lockdown.

36:28.447 --> 36:30.797
We'll start
the interrogations tomorrow.

36:30.840 --> 36:32.973
- I should've
figured it out sooner.

36:33.016 --> 36:34.931
- Lois, come on, you can't be
that hard on yourself.

36:34.975 --> 36:36.629
- I'm supposed to be
this incredible reporter,

36:36.672 --> 36:37.978
but I got fooled tonight,

36:38.021 --> 36:39.588
and someone almost murdered
my husband.

36:39.632 --> 36:40.937
- It's not that simple.

36:41.851 --> 36:45.420
I mean,
the guy's from another world.

36:45.464 --> 36:47.857
- I still think there's more
he's not telling us.

36:47.901 --> 36:49.207
- So do I.

36:51.296 --> 36:54.168
Which is why John Henry Irons
isn't going anywhere

36:54.212 --> 36:56.475
until we find out
everything he knows.

36:56.518 --> 36:59.260
- If it wasn't for the boys,

36:59.304 --> 37:00.827
you might've died tonight.

37:00.870 --> 37:02.089
- I got lucky

37:02.132 --> 37:04.178
Jordan's hearing clicked
when it did.

37:04.222 --> 37:06.093
- With everything this family
is facing,

37:06.136 --> 37:07.486
we can't rely on luck.

37:09.618 --> 37:11.141
You're right, Clark.

37:11.185 --> 37:12.273
We're not protecting the boys

37:12.317 --> 37:13.883
by keeping secrets from them.

37:14.797 --> 37:16.103
- So what do you
want to tell them?

37:17.931 --> 37:19.237
- Everything.

37:23.284 --> 37:24.720
[knocks]

37:26.200 --> 37:28.420
- Hey, I just--
I wanted to apologize

37:28.463 --> 37:30.683
for spying on you
and Sarah earlier.

37:36.341 --> 37:38.604
I...

37:38.647 --> 37:40.301
I'm really sorry

37:40.345 --> 37:42.521
you have to lie for me
like that all the time.

37:44.436 --> 37:47.482
- Actually, this time,
I kinda told the truth.

37:47.526 --> 37:49.876
I mean, not, like, all of it,
obviously, but...

37:51.443 --> 37:53.314
But somehow it--

37:53.358 --> 37:54.794
it almost felt worse this way,

37:54.837 --> 37:57.318
'cause it was, like, um,

37:57.362 --> 37:58.972
it's, like, I don't know.
Like, intentional.

38:03.281 --> 38:04.804
- It feels like everything
since we got here

38:04.847 --> 38:07.676
has just been a big secret.

38:08.198 --> 38:10.679
I just--I want it
to go back to normal so bad.

38:12.594 --> 38:14.988
- To be fair, Jordan, I mean,

38:15.031 --> 38:16.424
I'm pretty sure normal people
have stuff

38:16.468 --> 38:20.123
that they're hiding too.

38:20.167 --> 38:21.429
- Tonight's probably
been the most scared

38:21.473 --> 38:22.604
I've ever been in my life.

38:24.563 --> 38:28.654
- But gotta say,

38:28.697 --> 38:30.786
it was also pretty awesome.[laughs]

38:30.830 --> 38:32.266
- Yeah, okay,
you did total that truck.

38:32.310 --> 38:33.441
- Pretty sick.
Bro, I don't even have

38:33.485 --> 38:34.747
a learner's permit.

38:34.790 --> 38:36.052
- Or know how to drive!
- I know!

38:36.096 --> 38:39.621
- Which was incredibly reckless

38:39.665 --> 38:41.449
and dangerous

38:41.493 --> 38:44.104
and irresponsible

38:44.147 --> 38:47.281
and absolutely... necessary.

38:47.325 --> 38:49.152
You both saved my life tonight,

38:49.196 --> 38:51.024
so I think I owe you
a pretty big thank-you.

38:51.067 --> 38:53.374
- Listen, we know that you two
must have a lot of questions

38:53.418 --> 38:55.202
about what's been going on
around here.

38:56.246 --> 38:59.337
- Look, we've taught you
not to keep secrets from us.

38:59.380 --> 39:01.991
- So we're not gonna keep
secrets from you anymore.

39:02.035 --> 39:04.124
- Isn't most of that stuff,like,

39:04.167 --> 39:05.517
like, classified though?

39:05.560 --> 39:06.909
- Yes.

39:06.953 --> 39:09.172
Which is why none
of what we tell you

39:09.216 --> 39:12.045
can ever leave this house.
Is that understood?

39:13.220 --> 39:14.395
- Definitely.Yeah.

39:14.439 --> 39:16.092
[ethereal music]

39:16.136 --> 39:17.616
- All right,
who wants to go first?

39:17.659 --> 39:21.402
♪

39:21.446 --> 39:23.186
- What was that deal
with the guy tonight?

39:34.763 --> 39:36.765
- I just doubled the output
on the reflex modules,

39:36.809 --> 39:39.028
which means--
- We found Kal-El.

39:42.162 --> 39:45.121
It's time.
- Right now?

39:45.165 --> 39:46.514
But the tracking inlay's
still glitchy.

39:46.558 --> 39:48.081
- Nat--

39:48.124 --> 39:49.517
- And we haven't finished
the hammer yet,

39:49.561 --> 39:51.171
and the AI's still set
for Lex Luthor.

39:51.214 --> 39:53.608
- It doesn't matter who
the AI thinks is in the suit.

39:53.652 --> 39:55.393
It has to be now, Bug.

39:55.436 --> 39:58.308
[somber music]

39:58.352 --> 39:59.788
My ship will be here
in two minutes.

39:59.832 --> 40:01.399
♪

40:01.442 --> 40:04.445
Look, this is what
we've been preparing for.

40:04.489 --> 40:06.360
Our one chance to end it.

40:08.057 --> 40:09.885
- I just...

40:09.929 --> 40:11.974
I don't want anything
to happen to you.

40:14.368 --> 40:16.283
- I'm gonna go out there

40:16.326 --> 40:18.372
and kill him.

40:21.070 --> 40:23.116
And then I'm coming right back.

40:26.032 --> 40:28.034
Uh, say it with me.

40:29.644 --> 40:33.474
both: Forged in fire,
strong as steel.

40:46.574 --> 40:48.402
- I love you, Dad.

40:51.579 --> 40:53.363
- I love you too, Nat-Bug.

40:54.800 --> 40:56.671
More than anything
in this world.

41:00.153 --> 41:02.503
I'm gonna be right back.

41:14.907 --> 41:17.475
I promise.

41:25.787 --> 41:27.833
[door clicks shut]

41:31.880 --> 41:35.057
I'm gonna be right back.

41:35.101 --> 41:36.972
I promise.

41:39.540 --> 41:41.063
I'm gonna be right back.

41:43.283 --> 41:45.328
I promise.

41:45.372 --> 41:48.331
[dramatic music]

41:48.375 --> 41:53.598
♪

41:56.992 --> 41:59.952
[heroic music]

41:59.995 --> 42:07.046
♪

42:16.011 --> 42:19.058
- Greg, move your head.
